Package: sbyops
Type: Package
Title: Core Computational Engine for the Sabby Ecosystem
Version: 0.5.6
Authors@R: person("Joao B. G.", "de Brito", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "joaobatista.goncalvesdebrito@ugent.be")
Description: Serves as the foundational high-performance computing backbone 
    for the 'sabby' ecosystem, a suite designed for enterprise-grade 
    tabular data preprocessing. While the broader ecosystem provides 
    specialized modules for feature engineering, instance balancing, 
    row filtering, and persistent auditing, this package delivers the 
    low-level infrastructure. It features deeply optimized C++ and Fortran 
    native cores, automatic memory-safe execution strategies, and native 
    OpenMP parallelism. Built to handle massive analytical workloads, 
    it integrates direct linkage to Intel oneMKL and standard BLAS/LAPACK 
    libraries, explicitly engineered to support aggressive compiler optimizations.
